'''Shirley Carew Titus''' (April 28, 1892– March 21, 1967)  was a nurse educator at [[University of Michigan]] and [[Vanderbilt University School of Nursing]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|date=2007-01-01|title=Titus, Shirley Carew (1892–1967)|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G2-2588823410.html}}</ref> Titus was the executive director of the [[California Nurses Association/National Nurses Organizing Committee|California Nurses' Association]] from 1942 until 1956.<ref name=":0" /> She successfully advocated for and achieved the first [[collective bargaining]] for nurses.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nursingworld.org/FunctionalMenuCategories/AboutANA/Honoring-Nurses/NationalAwardsProgram/HallofFame/19761982/ShirleyCarewTitus.html|title=Shirley Carew Titus (1892-1967) 1982 Inductee|website=www.nursingworld.org|access-date=2016-07-01|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003132921/http://www.nursingworld.org/FunctionalMenuCategories/AboutANA/Honoring-Nurses/NationalAwardsProgram/HallofFame/19761982/ShirleyCarewTitus.html|archivedate=2016-10-03|df=}}</ref> In 1982, Titus was inducted into the [[American Nurses Association]] [[American Nurses Association Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]].<ref name=":1" />

